node.title: 'Scientifically unjustified': African leaders call for urgent lifting of Omicron travel bans
node.description: South African President Cyril Ramaphosa is calling on countries to "immediately and urgently" reverse travel bans following the discovery of the new coronavirus variant Omicron.

node.title: Border Force investigates after mystery yacht washes ashore
node.description: A search is underway off a remote coastline of eastern Victoria after a yacht is found with its radio on but no sign of anyone onboard.

node.title: Deaths of two people self-isolating in Auckland were potentially preventable, report finds
node.description: A review has found the deaths of two people with Covid-19 who were self-isolating at home in Auckland were potentially preventable.

node.title: Olympic Official Who Delivered Rio Games Sentenced to 30 Years for Bribery
node.description: Carlos Arthur Nuzman was found guilty after a trial that featured claims of rigged votes, gold bars and at least $2 million in payoffs to top sports officials.

node.title: Son who tried to dispel 'bad magic' contributed to mother's death during boating trip, coroner finds
node.description: Adrian Meneveau and his mother Felicity Loveday most likely died in the three days after they set sail in Melbourne's Port Phillip Bay. The pair's bodies have never been found, but the boat was later found empty and adrift.

node.title: Singer Katy Perry tried to 'snuff out' Australian fashion designer's business, court told
node.description: A court hears American singer Katy Perry used her "financial might" to try and shut down an Australian fashion designer's business called Katie Perry.

node.title: COVID-positive repatriation flight arrival to the NT tests positive for Omicron variant
node.description: A repatriation flight traveller to Darwin has tested positive for the Omicron COVID-19 variant. He is in quarantine at the Howard Springs quarantine facility.

node.title: KiwiSaver default funds not for everyone - financial consulting firm
node.description: Women could counter some of the lost earnings from the gender pay gap by switching out of a default KiwiSaver fund, according to a financial consulting firm.

node.title: Omicron: Will new measures against Covid variant work?
node.description: The new variant's genetic profile has raised concerns, but there's a shortage of real-world data, writes BBC science and health correspondent James Gallagher.

node.title: Covid-19 could spread through apartments' shared ventilation systems – expert
node.description: The potential spread of Covid-19 in apartments, particularly ones without windows that open, is raising alarm.

node.title: Rita Moreno on her life and career and the new "West Side Story" adaptation
node.description: Rita Moreno speaks with Bill Whitaker about the turmoil she went through early in her career, her 1961 portrayal of Anita in "West Side Story," and her new role in Steven Spielberg's upcoming adaptation of the Broadway classic.

node.title: How hazing led to the death of fraternity pledge Sam Martinez
node.description: Sam Martinez was a Washington State University freshman pledging a fraternity when a night of hazing led to his death. Anderson Cooper reports.

node.title: Doug Emhoff speaks at lighting of National Menorah
node.description: Sunday marks the first night of Hanukkah.

node.title: Military service members face deadline to get COVID-19 vaccine
node.description: U.S. Navy Surgeon General Rear Admiral Bruce Gillingham said that service members who do not get vaccinated "can be administratively separated for not following a direct order."

node.title: Italy and Portugal Could Meet for a 2022 World Cup Spot. Only One Can Go.
node.description: The draw for Europe’s final three qualifying places ensured that either Italy, the European champion, or Portugal, with Cristiano Ronaldo, would miss the finals in Qatar.

node.title: Carrie P. Meek, 5-Term Florida Representative, Dies at 95
node.description: She was the first Black person to represent the state in the House since Reconstruction, and she fought for programs to create jobs.

node.title: Snowstorm Leaves 61 Stranded in Remote U.K. Pub
node.description: A crowd had gathered on Friday night to listen to Noasis, an Oasis tribute band. On Sunday night, patrons, band members and staff members were still stuck.

node.title: Girl Taken From Home by Someone She Was Chatting With in Video Game: Police
node.description: The distressed teenager called her mother later the same day, saying she was hungry and had been taken far away.

node.title: In-demand Brandon Smith 'blown away' by Roosters
node.description: Melbourne's Brandon Smith says he was" blown away" by the Sydney Roosters and has made a call on his future but will first meet with Storm coach Craig Bellamy.

node.title: Government and telcos announce crackdown on scam text messages
node.description: Telecommunications companies will soon be able to block scam text messages from being sent in the first place, thanks to regulatory changes by the government.

node.title: Concerns about new COVID-19 variant see ASX fall
node.description: The ASX is in for a second day of losses as investors worry about the new COVID-19 variant Omicron.

node.title: NSW Omicron concerns grow, urgent tests for two more travellers
node.description: Health authorities in NSW are conducting urgent genomic sequencing to determine if two people who arrived in Sydney from southern Africa last night have the Omicron COVID-19 variant.

node.title: Booster vaccine time frames to be reviewed as COVID-19 Omicron variant appears in Australia
node.description: Health Minister Greg Hunt has asked the government's expert immunisation panel to review the time frame for when Australians should have a COVID-19 booster shot.

node.title: Two volunteer fire brigades suspended due to shortage of vaccinated crew
node.description: The small brigades do not have enough vaccinated volunteers to operate at full capacity and will be unable to operate from midnight.

node.title: N.F.L. Week 12 Predictions: Our Picks Against the Spread
node.description: Jonathan Taylor and the Colts make their postseason case against the Bucs, the Rams and Packers fight for a first-round bye, and the Dolphins try to extend their win streak against the Panthers.

node.title: Mike Lindell Accuses 'Attack Media' of 'Making a Mockery' of Proposed Election Lawsuit
node.description: "I'm frustrated. I've had it," the pro-Trump CEO said Sunday after his much-touted Supreme Court lawsuit wasn't filed by his self-imposed deadline.

node.title: More stores mistakenly sell recalled sugar products
node.description: Both of New Zealand's two major supermarket companies have now had contaminated sugar mistakenly sold after it made its way onto supermarket shelves after a recall.

node.title: Finance and investment firms join in plan for community housing
node.description: A trio of finance and investment concerns are combining to back a $200 million investment in community housing.

node.title: Radius Care reports lower half-year profit
node.description: Higher wage costs and the recent Covid-19 lockdown have weighed on The aged care operator's half-year profit.

node.title: Demand boosts Oceania Healthcare profits
node.description: Aged care service provider Oceania Healthcare has reported a strong lift in first half profit, driven by increased demand for independent living apartments and villas.
